## Overview

Total C.A.M. Solutions is an Australian-owned and operated company established in 1999. Based in Perth, we are a leading provider of precision CNC engineering and machining services.
We specialise in delivering high-quality CNC machining using advanced 5-axis technology, enabling us to manufacture complex components with exceptional accuracy and efficiency.
With decades of industry experience, Total C.A.M. Solutions is committed to providing reliable, high-precision solutions for a wide range of industries across Perth and beyond.
Our CNC machining services deliver exceptional precision and efficiency for a broad range of cylindrical components. Using advanced multi-axis technology, we produce intricate geometries and complex features while maintaining tight tolerances.
Our fleet of 24 CNC machines is equipped to handle a wide variety of materials, from exotic steels through to plastics, ensuring versatility for your projects. Our automated processes enhance production speed and consistency, making us the ideal manufacturing partner for industries such as mining, oil & gas, fire protection, and marine, among others.

## Capabilities

As an Australian owned CNC precision machining workshop, Total C.A.M
Solutions specialises in CNC Milling, CNC Turning and EDM Wire-cutting to
support a wide range of market sectors and industries in Perth, Western
Australia. We pride ourselves on our high-quality engineering solutions, strict
quality control, highly experienced team and satisfied customers.
With our CNC machining workshop operating from Wangara, 25 minutes
outside Perth CBD, we are able to serve customers Australia wide.
We have a highly-skilled, knowledgeable, and experienced team who can
cover a wide range of disciplines by integrating the latest CAD/CAM software,
tooling, holding and cutting techniques. This gives us the capability to
produce the most complex components, on time and on budget.
• CNC Milling – Capacity 2100mm x 670mm
• CNC Turning – Capacity – 580mm x 2000 mm
• CNC Slotting – Capacity – 60mm x 400 Deep Keyway
• EDM Wire Cutting
• Marking & Engraving
• Slotting and Spline Cutting
• Surface Grinding
• Specialised Threads
• Drafting engineering drawings
• 3D Solid modelling
